<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/237: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-29T17:00:00-04:00">May 29, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>43. Your 37, May 26, noon. What is the meaning of the phrase “the release
                            of these guarantees is subject to the Hague agreements,” particularly as
                            the Hague agreements are understood to have come into force before date
                            of Italian statement?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>